<p>The <b>two envelopes problem</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Puzzle" title="Puzzle">puzzle</a> or <a href="/wiki/Paradox" title="Paradox">paradox</a> within the <a href="/wiki/Bayesian_probability" title="Bayesian probability">subjectivistic interpretation</a> of <a href="/wiki/Probability" title="Probability">probability theory</a>; more specifically within <a href="/wiki/Decision_theory#Choice_under_uncertainty" title="Decision theory">Bayesian decision theory</a>. This is still an open problem among the subjectivists as no consensus has been reached yet.</p>
